  "prompt": "How do you get good letters of recommendation?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for getting strong letters of recommendation:\n\n1. Choose recommenders who know you well\n- People who can speak specifically about your skills and character\n- Past professors, employers, mentors who have worked closely with you\n\n2. Build good relationships\n- Engage actively in class or work\n- Show genuine interest and enthusiasm\n- Be professional and reliable\n\n3. Give recommenders plenty of time\n- Ask at least 4-6 weeks before deadline\n- Provide all necessary information and forms\n- Make the process easy for them\n\n4. Provide helpful background information\n- Give them your resume\n- Explain the purpose of the recommendation\n- Highlight achievements they might mention\n- Remind them of specific projects or accomplishments\n\n5. Follow up and be appreciative\n- Send a thank you note\n- Let them know the outcome of your application\n- Keep them informed\n\n6. Prepare materials in advance\n- Transcript\n- List of accomplishments\n- Addressed, stamped envelopes\n- Application details\n\n7. Be selective about who you ask\n- Choose people who will write positive, detailed letters\n- Avoid asking someone who doesn't know you well\n\n8. Waive your right to view the letter\n- Shows confidence and allows for more honest recommendations",
